# 1️⃣ What is an API?
API (Application Programming Interface) is a communication method that allows two applications to exchange data.

Instead of testing UI screens, API testing validates the backend functionality directly.

---

# 2️⃣ API Testing vs UI Testing

| Feature | API Testing | UI Testing |
|--------|------------|------------|
| Speed | Faster | Slower |
| Stability | More stable | UI changes can break tests |
| Coverage | Backend validation | Frontend validation |
| Execution | Lightweight | Requires browser setup |

---

# 3️⃣ Client-Server Architecture
API testing is based on request-response model:

- Client sends request (Postman)
- Server processes request
- Server returns response (JSON/XML)

---

# 4️⃣ HTTP Methods Practiced
The following REST API methods were learned and executed:

### ✅ GET
Used to retrieve data from server.

### ✅ POST
Used to create new data.

### ✅ PUT
Used to update complete existing data.

### ✅ PATCH
Used to update partial data.

### ✅ DELETE
Used to remove existing data.

